    "narrative": "Our primary offensive engine today centers on **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands an elite score of 81.57 against Arrighetti. With a generous 5.10 xERA opponent and a favorable dynamic platoon split, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is the clear daily ceiling play, especially given his high-upside matchup against a slow-delivery pitcher that boosts his stolen base potential. Joining him in the \"Strong\" start tier are **Will Smith** (72.25) and **Lawrence Butler** (66.55). **Will Smith** benefits from a massive park-factor lift and a plus-matchup against the vulnerable Quintana, while **Lawrence Butler** is buoyed by significant SP skill advantages that offset his lower lineup placement. Even with a tentative #8 spot, **Lawrence Butler** remains a lock given his elite platoon profile today.\n\nThe most difficult lineup decision centered on the utilization of **Daulton Varsho** (40.47) and **Cal Raleigh** (49.58). **Daulton Varsho** barely cleared the floor, hamstrung by a brutal matchup against the crafty Detmers and a negative platoon split that neutralized his power potential. He was nearly pushed to the bench in favor of **Cal Raleigh**, whose xwOBA metrics remain superior; however, **Cal Raleigh** ultimately secured the UTIL spot despite his own unfavorable park factor because of the massive potential of hitting second in the order against Ginn. Meanwhile, **Bryson Stott** (64.57) warrants attention; despite being held back slightly by an elite holding pitcher, his dynamic platoon edge against Rea makes him a vital start in our pursuit of scarce stolen bases. Owners should monitor the lineup statuses of **Lawrence Butler** and **Daulton Varsho** closely, as any further demotion in the batting order would push both toward the bench to preserve our game caps.",
